{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Pre-Push Validation",
  "description": "When the agent stops, shows a summary of all changes, validates branch naming convention (type/descricao-curta) and commit message format (Conventional Commits), and asks for explicit confirmation before pushing.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentStop"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Before finishing, perform pre-push validation:\n\n1. Run `git log --oneline -10` to show recent commits.\n2. Run `git branch --show-current` to check the current branch.\n3. Run `git diff --stat HEAD~1` (or appropriate range) to show files changed.\n4. Present a summary to the user:\n   - Current branch name\n   - List of commits made during this session\n   - Files changed\n5. Validate branch name:\n   - If branch follows type/descricao pattern (feat/, fix/, refactor/, chore/, docs/, etc.): ✅ \"Branch segue o padrão Conventional Commits.\"\n   - If NOT: ⚠️ \"ATENÇÃO: A branch '{name}' NÃO segue o padrão type/descricao. Considere renomear antes de fazer push.\"\n6. Validate commit messages:\n   - Check if recent commits follow Conventional Commits pattern: type(scope?): descrição\n   - If NOT: ⚠️ warn about non-conforming commits.\n7. Ask the user: \"Deseja fazer push desta branch? (Sim/Não)\"\n8. Only if user explicitly confirms, run `git push origin <branch-name>`.\n9. If user declines, acknowledge and finish without pushing.\n\nIMPORTANT: NEVER push without explicit user confirmation."
  }
}